            window.DMPlaceholder = {
  laterQueue: []
};
window.DM = window.DM || {
  later: function (eventNames, callback) {
    if (!callback && 'Promise' in window) {
      return new Promise(function (resolve) {
        window.DMPlaceholder.laterQueue.push({
          callback: resolve,
          eventNames: eventNames
        });
      });
    } else {
      return window.DMPlaceholder.laterQueue.push({
        callback: callback,
        eventNames: eventNames
      });
    }
  }
};
window.isAdFreeEntitled = function () {
  try {
    var afstatus = JSON.parse(window.localStorage.getItem('mol-fe-paywall-status'));

    if (window.PageCriteria && window.PageCriteria.geo === 'US') {
      return false;
    }

    return !afstatus.invalidated && !afstatus.deviceDisabled && afstatus.validUntil > Date.now();
  } catch (error) {}

  return false;
};

    <div class="gamma">
        <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
   <meta itemprop="position" content="1"> 
  <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
    <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10510775/Tories-say-West-threaten-block-Moscows-banks.html">Last push for peace: Boris and Biden agree 'a window for diplomacy' in Ukraine remains open and call for Putin to 'step back from threats' amid continued fears Russia will attack on Wednesday&nbsp;</a>
  </h2>
  <a href="/news/article-10510775/Tories-say-West-threaten-block-Moscows-banks.html">
    
     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/964x580_MP4_6817865237526198816.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/308x174_JPG_6817865237526198816.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="172" data-frame-count="70" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/636x382_JPG-HD_6817865237526198816.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="358" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-fps="7" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/964x580_JPG-SINGLE_6817865237526198816.jpg" class=" b-loaded" width="964" height="542"><video loop="" muted="true" playsinline="true" style="height: 542px; width: 964px; display: none;"><source src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/964x580_MP4_6817865237526198816.mp4" type="video/mp4"></video>
   
<noscript>
    <img src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6817865237526198816/964x580_JPG-SINGLE_6817865237526198816.jpg" width="964" height=542 />
</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
      <p>
        
        Boris Johnson (right) shared a 40-minute phone call with US President Joe Biden this evening in which the allied leaders agreed there is still hope for a diplomatic solution to the situation in Ukraine. It comes after Mr Johnson earlier today warned there could be less than 48 hours to stop an invasion. The PM is set to embark on another trip to Europe later this week as diplomatic efforts ramp up to defuse the standoff with Russia. Chancellor Olaf Scholz has been in Kyiv today and will go to Moscow tomorrow. The UK, EU and US have set out brutal options for sanctions including starving Russia of foreign capital, holding up the Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline and targeting banks and oligarchs close to the Kremlin. But there is not yet a clear package agreed across Nato allies, with Germany among the countries seen as dragging their heels. Defence Secretary Ben Walllace revealed his frustration at the weekend by warning there was a 'whiff of Munich in the air' - a reference to the appeasement of Hitler. Mr Johnson took a thinly-veiled swipe today insisting that 'the world needs to learn the lesson of 2014' when not enough was done to move away from Russian gas and oil following the Russian activity in eastern Ukraine and the annexation of Crimea.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

                          <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-large cleared" data-original-title="NatWest to close 21 branches and RBS to shut 11 amid shift to mobile banking">
   <meta itemprop="position" content="2"> 
  <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
    <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511507/NatWest-close-21-branches-RBS-shut-11-amid-shift-mobile-banking.html">MORE High Street banks to close: NatWest will shut 21 branches across UK while RBS will close 11 amid shift to mobile banking&nbsp;</a>
  </h2>
  <a href="/news/article-10511507/NatWest-close-21-branches-RBS-shut-11-amid-shift-mobile-banking.html">
         <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/18/article-10511507-54190563-790_308x424.jpg" alt="NatWest to close 21 branches and RBS to shut 11 amid shift to mobile banking" style="max-width:100%" width="308" height="424">
    
    
    
    
      <noscript>
    
        <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/18/article-10511507-54190563-790_308x424.jpg" height="424" width="308" alt="NatWest to close 21 branches and RBS to shut 11 amid shift to mobile banking" />
    
      </noscript>
    
  </a>
  <div class="articletext-holder">
    <p>
      
      The banking giant has confirmed the sites, the majority of which are in England, will be closing, but are yet to provide a date as to when. The list of branches due to close includes the Royal Bank of Scotland branch inside NatWest's headquarters in Bishopsgate, central London. Most staff will be relocated to other branches, but the bank said 12 jobs will be put at risk. A statement from NatWest said: 'As with many industries, most of our customers are shifting to mobile and online banking, because it's faster and easier for people to manage their financial lives.'
    </p>
    <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">

     <meta itemprop="position" content="7"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10510603/Victory-REBEKAH-latest-round-Wagatha-Christie-war.html">Coleen tells Rebekah Vardy agent 'I'll see you in court': Rooney threatens to sue Caroline Watt AFTER £1m 'Wagatha Christie' libel case and says she is 'looking forward' to seeing her WhatsApp messages as judge orders new trawl&nbsp;</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10510603/Victory-REBEKAH-latest-round-Wagatha-Christie-war.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/54182549-0-image-a-12_1644852281466.jpg" alt="Coleen tells Rebekah Vardy agent 'I'll see you in court'" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/54182549-0-image-a-12_1644852281466.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Coleen tells Rebekah Vardy agent 'I'll see you in court'" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Coleen Rooney (pictured centre and left) today lost the latest battle in her long-running Wagatha Christie war with Becky Vardy (pictured right with husband Jamie) after she was refused permission to add her rival's agent to the lawsuit. Ms Rooney's lawyers previously claimed that Mrs Vardy had leaked information to The Sun either directly or through her agent Caroline Watt 'acting on her instruction or with her knowing approval'. She asked for permission to bring an 'additional claim' against Ms Watt for misuse of private information and wanted it to be heard alongside the libel case. In a ruling on Monday, following a two-day hearing last week, Mrs Justice Steyn refused permission for the additional claim against Ms Watt. The two warring WAGs are now set for a legal showdown in May after the High Court judge ruled on key areas that could decide the case and insisted that it needed to be settled at a full trial as quickly as possible. The judge gave the go-ahead for Ms Rooney to amend her defence case to include an allegation that Ms Vardy, through Ms Watt, provided information to The Sun about an unnamed professional footballer. She also gave permission for disclosure of WhatsApp messages between Mrs Vardy and Ms Watt during the relevant period, and allowed Ms Rooney's application for an order that both parties make a joint request for information to Instagram. She refused other disclosure applications made by both Ms Rooney and Mrs Vardy.&nbsp;
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/12/54175597-0-image-a-6_1644840850061.jpg" alt="Horrified father watched rugby star son suffer fatal injury on LIVESTREAM from his iPad" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/12/54175597-0-image-a-6_1644840850061.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Horrified father watched rugby star son suffer fatal injury on LIVESTREAM from his iPad" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Jack Jeffery, 27,&nbsp;was injured while scoring a try for Evesham in their match against Berkswell and Balsall at their ground in Warwickshire on Saturday. He was taken to&nbsp;University Hospital Coventry but later died from his injuries. His family paid tribute to Jack, saying he 'enriched the lives of everyone who was lucky to know and have met him'. His sister Daisy said he 'never got back up' after scoring an 'amazing try' on Saturday afternoon, while his father Glenn said he died 'doing the thing that he loved the most, playing rugby'. Glenn told The Sun: 'When he failed to get up it was clear there was some sort of problem but the other players didn't seem to be worried, so I wasn't. They thought it was a head injury and he would come around... he was in and out of consciousness but at some point his heart stopped for 30 minutes. He lost a huge amount of blood and despite [doctors'] best efforts, they could not save him and he died in theatre.'
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div class="home item gradient_divide module">
  <div class="gradient-split wocc link-wocc linkro-wocc">
  <h6>
      RUSSIA-UKRAINE ON THE BRINK OF WAR
  </h6>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
</div>

</div>

    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511173/A-pretext-war-Russian-TV-propagandists-claim-thousands-civilians-tortured-savagely-killed-Ukraine-amid-invasion-fears-Moscow-threatens-FIRE-ships-waters-submarine-row.html">Biden CLOSES the US embassy in Kiev and moves it to western Ukraine as he orders destruction of its computers because of 'accelerated' buildup of Russian troops</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10511173/A-pretext-war-Russian-TV-propagandists-claim-thousands-civilians-tortured-savagely-killed-Ukraine-amid-invasion-fears-Moscow-threatens-FIRE-ships-waters-submarine-row.html">

              <noscript>

              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            The move will put U.S. diplomats far to the south of where Putin is amassing thousands of troops in Belarus and hundreds of miles from where the U.S. says Putin has stationed a force of well over 100,000 troops. Blinken attributed the move to the 'dramatic acceleration in the buildup of Russian forces,' which continued over the weekend. 'I have no higher priority than the safety and security of Americans around the world, and that, of course, includes our colleagues serving at our posts overseas,' Blinken said in a statement announcing the move of personnel to about 50 miles from the Polish border.&nbsp;
        </p>

        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511269/Ukraine-tensions-Putin-keeps-ministers-arms-length-amid-fears-war.html">Deploy the long table! Now Putin keeps his own ministers a safe distance away as Moscow says there is 'a chance' for progress in Ukraine talks to avoid war</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10511269/Ukraine-tensions-Putin-keeps-ministers-arms-length-amid-fears-war.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/article-10511269-54182501-931_636x660.jpg" alt="Ukraine tensions: Putin keeps ministers at arm's length amid fears of war" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="660">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/article-10511269-54182501-931_636x660.jpg" height="660" width="636" alt="Ukraine tensions: Putin keeps ministers at arm's length amid fears of war" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Sergei Lavrov and Sergei Shoigu, Russia's foreign and defence ministers, were both long-tabled during meetings with Putin on Monday as they discussed tensions on the border with Ukraine (top, Lavrov meets with the Russian president). it comes a week after Macron was given the same treatment after travelling to Moscow for talks aimed at avoiding war. During his meeting today, Lavrov urged Putin to allow more time for negotiations with Western powers - saying he is preparing to respond to American offers of arms control treaties and there is 'a chance' of getting results. Washington is warning that Putin could be just hours away from ordering an invasion of Ukraine, after massing 148,000 troops on the border while issuing a list of security demands that the West has largely dismissed.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

        <a href="/news/article-10511227/PE-teacher-22-struck-accused-sleeping-18-year-old-pupil.html">

              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>

Miss Tweedie, who is now 27, allegedly slept with the 18-year-old pupil after the leavers night at SWG3 in Glasgow in June 2017. The GTCS did not find this allegation proven on the weight of evidence presented to the panel but issued Miss Tweedie with a removal order after finding her conduct fell significantly short of the standard expected of a registered teacher.
        </p>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="36"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511795/UKs-paid-public-sector-diversity-chief-Network-Rail-director-164K-taxpayer-funded-salary.html">Revealed: UK's top-paid public sector diversity chief is a Network Rail director on £164,000 taxpayer-funded salary who blasted Boris - who she earns more than - for 'white privilege'</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10511795/UKs-paid-public-sector-diversity-chief-Network-Rail-director-164K-taxpayer-funded-salary.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/19/54191131-0-image-a-8_1644865393382.jpg" alt="UK's top-paid public sector diversity chief is Network Rail director on £164K" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/19/54191131-0-image-a-8_1644865393382.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="UK's top-paid public sector diversity chief is Network Rail director on £164K" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Loraine Martins (left), the UK's top-paid public sector diversity chief at Network Rail, earns up to £164,999 a year and previously shared an article (inset) accusing Boris Johnson (right) of 'white privilege'. Data released by the government shows Martins is paid a minimum of £160,000 which can rise to a maximum of £164,999, meaning she could earn more than the Prime Minister whose yearly earning is capped at almost £162,000. In 2018, she used her Twitter account to share a comment piece from the Guardian which accused Boris Johnson, then foreign secretary, of 'white privilege'. And in April 2021, she retweeted a post from television presenter Adil Ray who accused the government of 'corruption', according to the publication Guido Fawkes , although the retweet has since been removed. According to the Women at Work online summit, Martins' role includes overseeing 'a centre of expertise which supports Network Rail's ambition to be a more open, diverse and inclusive business'.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

  </h2>

     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/7975451901786342834/636x382_MP4_7975451901786342834.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/7975451901786342834/308x174_JPG_7975451901786342834.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="26" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/7975451901786342834/636x382_JPG-HD_7975451901786342834.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="26" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/7975451901786342834/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7975451901786342834.jpg" width="636" height="382">

    <img src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/7975451901786342834/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7975451901786342834.jpg" width="636" height=382 />
</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
     <p>
       
       The 66-year-old host missed just eight episodes after ABC announced it was benching the comedian for two weeks - presumably ten episodes - following her last broadcast on January 31, where she apologized for saying the Holocaust was 'not about race' on the previous day's show. But on Monday, Goldberg was back on the air after missing just eight shows. ABC did not immediately return a comment regarding her early return as of Monday afternoon. 'Well, hello, hello, hello and welcome to The View. And yes, I am back… And I missed you all, too,' Goldberg said to viewers and her co-hosts at the top of the show. 'I've got to tell you, there's something kind of marvelous about being on a show like this, because we are The View and this is what we do. And sometimes we don't do it as delicately as we could.' 'But it's five minutes to get in important information about topics. And that's what we try to do every day. And I want to thank everybody who reached out while I was away,' she continued.
     </p>

                <div class="home item gradient_divide module">
  <div class="gradient-split wocc link-wocc linkro-wocc">
  <h6>
      SUPER BOWL LVI
  </h6>
  <div>&nbsp;</div>
</div>

</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="64"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10509499/Prince-Harry-leaves-Meghan-home-attend-Super-Bowl-cousin-Princess-Eugenie.html">Where's Meghan? Prince Harry and Princess Eugenie join Hollywood's royalty - including Kendall Jenner, Beyonce and Katy Perry - to watch the LA Rams triumph over Cincinnati Bengals in dramatic Super Bowl</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10509499/Prince-Harry-leaves-Meghan-home-attend-Super-Bowl-cousin-Princess-Eugenie.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/11/article-10509499-54170129-455_636x576.jpg" alt="Prince Harry leaves Meghan at home to attend Super Bowl with cousin Princess Eugenie" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="576">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/11/article-10509499-54170129-455_636x576.jpg" height="576" width="636" alt="Prince Harry leaves Meghan at home to attend Super Bowl with cousin Princess Eugenie" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Prince Harry watched last night's dramatic Super Bowl in Los Angeles with his cousin Princess Eugenie alongside a host of Hollywood stars including Kendall Jenner, Jay-Z and Justin Bieber. The 37-year-old sat in the stands with his cousin at the SoFi Stadium to see the Los Angeles Rams beat the Cincinnati Bengals 23-20 in a fourth-quarter comeback at Super Bowl LVI - but there was no sign of Meghan. Harry and Eugenie, 31, sat in luxurious leather seats inside a private box at the stadium and wore face coverings in accordance with Los Angeles County rules which require KN95 or N95-grade masks for large outdoor events. The presence of the two royals at the star-studded event - which also hosted the likes of Ryan Reynolds, LeBron James, Kevin Hart, Charlize Theron, Rebel Wilson, Ellen DeGeneres and more - was announced by the NFL, whose UK Twitter account shared a photo of them and wrote: 'Prince Harry and Princess Eugenie in the house at #SBLVI.' Also pictured at last night's game: Emily Ratajkowski (top left), Ben Affleck and Jennifer Lopez (bottom left), and Justin Bieber, Hailey Bieber and Kendall Jenner (bottom right).
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="71"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10510671/Super-Bowl-Princess-Eugenie-visits-Prince-Harry-Los-Angeles.html">Why Princess Eugenie broke ranks to become the FIRST royal to visit Harry in LA after Megxit: Prince's closest ally in 'The Firm' joins him to watch Super Bowl</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10510671/Super-Bowl-Princess-Eugenie-visits-Prince-Harry-Los-Angeles.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/11/54174989-0-image-a-31_1644839681411.jpg" alt="Super Bowl: Princess Eugenie visits Prince Harry in Los Angeles" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/11/54174989-0-image-a-31_1644839681411.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Super Bowl: Princess Eugenie visits Prince Harry in Los Angeles" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Princess Eugenie has become the first member of the Royal Family to make a public visit to Prince Harry in California two years after he quit as a senior royal, as they were seen attending last night's Super Bowl alongside a host of Hollywood stars including Kendall Jenner, Jay-Z and Justin Bieber - but there was no sign of Meghan. The cousins sat in the premium seats at the SoFi Stadium in Los Angeles as concern mounts back in Britain over the Duke of Sussex's forthcoming tell-all biography overshadowing his grandmother the Queen's Platinum Jubilee. Some Twitter users initially mistook Eugenie for Meghan, but the Duchess was not there. The couple, who wed in 2018 and live nearby in a $14million Montecito mansion, are parents to Archie, two, and eight month-old Lilibet - so it is likely that Meghan was at home looking after the children while her husband went to the showpiece game. Meghan is also close to Eugenie having been introduced to her before she had even met Harry, through their mutual friend Misha Nonoo. It therefore seems possible that Eugenie could be staying with the Sussexes in the US. Harry, 37, and Eugenie, 31, have been friends since childhood despite their six-year age gap and are known to still get on well despite the Duke's removal from royal public life in Britain and his repeated attacks on his wider family. And Eugenie's visit will be viewed by some observers as a potential effort to rebuild broken bridges between Harry and the rest of the family - with an important series of royal occasions coming up over the next few months. Also pictured: Harry and Eugenie together in 2012 (top right) and 2007 (bottom right) in London.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/3665884218035256516/636x382_MP4_3665884218035256516.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/3665884218035256516/308x174_JPG_3665884218035256516.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="68" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/3665884218035256516/636x382_JPG-HD_3665884218035256516.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="68" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/3665884218035256516/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_3665884218035256516.jpg" width="636" height="382">

</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
     <p>
       
       Netflix bosses released the season two teaser trailer on Valentine's Day ahead of the show's March 25 return. Sharing the promo on social media on Monday with the words 'love never plays by the rules,' the clip opens with the voice of Lady Whistledown, the&nbsp;infamous gossip columnist, as narrated by Julie Andrews, as she says: 'Dearest gentle reader, did you miss me? 'As the members of our ton questioned my identity and means, this author has been doing but one thing.
     </p>

                            <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-small">
  <meta itemprop="position" content="83">
  <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
    <a itemprop="url" href="/sciencetech/article-10510467/Astronomers-Germany-discovered-strange-new-type-star.html">Astronomers discover a new type of 'FREAK STAR' covered in helium-burning ashes that may have been formed by a rare stellar merger event&nbsp;</a>
  </h2>
  <div class="articletext">
    <a href="/sciencetech/article-10510467/Astronomers-Germany-discovered-strange-new-type-star.html">
           <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/10/54171627-0-image-a-93_1644834715495.jpg" alt="" style="max-width:100%" width="154" height="115">
      
      
      
      
        <noscript>
      
          <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/10/54171627-0-image-a-93_1644834715495.jpg" height="115" width="154" alt="" />
      
        </noscript>
      
    </a>
    <p>
        
        It's thought that this new type of star was formed by the merger of two white dwarfs -&nbsp;the hot, dense remnants of long-dead stars, report scientists in Tübingen, Germany.
    </p>
  </div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="85"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10509927/Russian-skater-15-CLEARED-continue-Olympics-despite-testing-positive-banned-drug.html">Final nail in the coffin for Beijing's shameful Winter Olympics: Outrage as Russian skater Kamila Valieva, 15, is CLEARED to continue at Games because banning her over doping claims 'would cause her irreparable harm'&nbsp;</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10509927/Russian-skater-15-CLEARED-continue-Olympics-despite-testing-positive-banned-drug.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/09/54169535-0-image-a-23_1644831128771.jpg" alt="Final nail in the coffin for Beijing's farcical Winter Olympics: Russian skater, 15, is" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/09/54169535-0-image-a-23_1644831128771.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Final nail in the coffin for Beijing's farcical Winter Olympics: Russian skater, 15, is" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Teenage Russian ice skater Kamila Valieva has been cleared to continue to compete at the Beijing Winter Olympics despite testing positive for a banned drug. The 15-year-old landed the first ever quadruple jump by a woman at the Winter Olympics, to win gold for the Russian team last week. But the following day the medal ceremony was put on hold when results from a test on December 25 last year found she had taken the banned substance, trimetazidine, that can enhance performance. However she has today been told it would be unfair to suspend her from the Olympics by the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) after a near six hour grilling in Beijing by video. The CAS panel ruled that a suspension could cause her 'irreparable harm' and said the youngster can continue to perform due to the 'exceptional circumstances' of her case. It added that Valieva was 'protected person' under the World Anti-Doping Code. Valieva (pictured taking tumble in training today) is now free to take part in the women's individual figure skating competition on Tuesday, in which she is favourite for gold.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/femail/article-10511625/Models-strut-catwalk-TAPE-New-York-Fashion-Week.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/18/54189597-0-image-a-212_1644862278697.jpg" alt="Models strut down the catwalk in nothing but TAPE at New York Fashion Week" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/18/54189597-0-image-a-212_1644862278697.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Models strut down the catwalk in nothing but TAPE at New York Fashion Week" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            The Miami-based Black Tape Project - known for its daring styles and for bringing&nbsp;new meaning to the phrase 'less is more' - showcased one of its most revealing collections. Bikinis made entirely out of tape were on display during the show, held on Sunday at The Ziegfeld Ballroom during the week-long event, which started on February 11 this year and will run until February 16. 'King of Tape' Joel Alvarez founded fashion brand Black Tape Project back in 2008 and usually uses a spectrum of different tapes - including mirrored and metallics - to create his daring designs.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="99"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511049/The-cathartic-Beatles-pictures-helped-Ringo-Starr-lockdown.html">The 'cathartic' Beatles pictures that helped Ringo Starr get through lockdown: Fascinating rarely-seen images of the Fab Four that drummer compiled during pandemic</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10511049/The-cathartic-Beatles-pictures-helped-Ringo-Starr-lockdown.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/16/54185413-0-image-a-31_1644856468524.jpg" alt="The 'cathartic' Beatles pictures that helped Ringo Starr get through lockdown" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/16/54185413-0-image-a-31_1644856468524.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="The 'cathartic' Beatles pictures that helped Ringo Starr get through lockdown" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            The legendary drummer (pictured left and, recently, inset) , now aged 81, compiled the rarely-seen images of himself with John Lennon, Paul McCartney and George Harrison as part of an uplifting project. He sourced and researched the photos, many of which were taken by fans, and secured permission to publish them. The behind-the-scenes images chart the very beginning of the Fab Four, through to the height of Beatlemania, touring America and then the tensions that culminated in the world's biggest band splitting up. They have been put together in the book 'Lifted: Fab Images and Memories in My Life With The Beatles From Across the Universe' that is due to be released today. A limited number of 1,000 have been signed by Sir Ringo and cost £365 ($495) each. Also pictured: George Harrison, Sir Paul McCartney, John Lennon and&nbsp; Sir Ringo in Washington DC (top right) at the height of their success as the Beatles in the 1960s; Sir Paul, Harrison, Lennon and Sir Ringo are seen during their Magical Mystery Tour (bottom right).
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="106"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10511405/Boris-Johns-Photo-ops-leave-PM-looking-like-North-Koreas-Kim.html">It's Boris Wrong-un! The Prime Minister's love of a photo-op suggests his spin doctors have been copying direct from the propaganda playbook of North Korean dictator Kim Jong Un&nbsp;</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10511405/Boris-Johns-Photo-ops-leave-PM-looking-like-North-Koreas-Kim.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/17/article-10511405-54185331-818_636x550.jpg" alt="Photos of Boris Johnson looking like North Korea's Kim Jong Un" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="550">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/17/article-10511405-54185331-818_636x550.jpg" height="550" width="636" alt="Photos of Boris Johnson looking like North Korea's Kim Jong Un" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Boris Johnson and Kim Jong-un - two men with instantly recognisable haridos, a love of the finer things in life and a history of womanizing who also share a love of a good photo op. That has led to some strikingly similar photos of the two men emerging over the years, as this MailOnline compilation shows. Supreme Leader Johns-un can be seen offering field guidance to shipyard workers (top left), at a food factory (second left), on horseback (second right) and sitting in the cockpit of a fighter jet (top right) whilst Kim can be seen doing... almost the exact same things as part of North Korean propaganda.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

  </h2>
  <div class="articletext">
    <a href="/sciencetech/article-10509217/Small-pets-risk-heatstroke-especially-global-temperatures-rise-study.html">
           <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/08/54167599-0-image-m-28_1644827567637.jpg" alt="" style="max-width:100%" width="154" height="115">
      
      
      
      
        <noscript>
      
          <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/08/54167599-0-image-m-28_1644827567637.jpg" height="115" width="154" alt="" />
      
        </noscript>
      
    </a>
    <p>
        
        A new study led by Nottinham Trent University suggests that as well as man's best friend, cats, guinea pigs, rabbits and ferrets are also being taken to vets with the condition.
    </p>
  </div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="120"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10510911/Britains-Jacuzzi-Eight-tap-spray-tub-claimed-one-UKs-whirlpool-baths.html">Britain's 'first Jacuzzi': Eight-tap spray tub that wealthy Somerset estate owner bought for his wife in the 1890s as 'Valentine's Day gift' is claimed to be one of UK's first whirlpool baths</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10510911/Britains-Jacuzzi-Eight-tap-spray-tub-claimed-one-UKs-whirlpool-baths.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/12/54176003-0-image-a-49_1644842844314.jpg" alt="Britain's 'first Jacuzzi': Eight-tap spray tub is claimed to be one of UK's first" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/12/54176003-0-image-a-49_1644842844314.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Britain's 'first Jacuzzi': Eight-tap spray tub is claimed to be one of UK's first" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            The eight-tap spray whirlpool bath (left) was ordered by millionaire Edward Portman (right) in the 1890s - possibly as a Valentine's Day present - at the grand Hestercombe House (inset) as a gift for his wife Constance (circled right). It boasts settings including 'wave', 'plunge', 'spray' and 'douche', and although it has not been used for years, is still in full working order - making it among the best-preserved in the UK. It cost Portman around £45 - the equivalent of £5,000 in today's money - to have the bath fitted. It was designed and installed by George Jennings Ltd, the firm founded by the engineer of the same name who invented the first public flush toilets. The bath is now set to be shown off as part of an exhibition of the Hestercombe estate, which is set across more than 100 acres near Taunton.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="123"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/femail/article-10510167/Can-guess-15-hidden-love-songs-minute.html">Can YOU guess the 15 hidden love songs in under a minute? Tricky Valentine's Day picture quiz will put music fans to the test&nbsp;</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/femail/article-10510167/Can-guess-15-hidden-love-songs-minute.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/08/54167213-0-image-a-3_1644826708734.jpg" alt="Can YOU guess the 15 hidden love songs in under a minute?" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/08/54167213-0-image-a-3_1644826708734.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Can YOU guess the 15 hidden love songs in under a minute?" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            A new say-what-you-see puzzle was created by gift provider Watches2U to celebrate the most romantic day of the year, and includes well-known love songs from popular artists. The hits include classic love songs by Elvis and Frankie Vallie, as well as more modern offerings by Beyonce and Bruno Mars. The current record to beat is one minute - so, how quickly can you name all 15 songs?
        </p>

  </h2>
  <a href="/news/article-10510159/A-ghost-tips-customers-pint-300-year-old-haunted-pub-Video.html">
    
     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6176517293721499259/636x382_MP4_6176517293721499259.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6176517293721499259/308x174_JPG_6176517293721499259.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="38" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6176517293721499259/636x382_JPG-HD_6176517293721499259.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="38" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6176517293721499259/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_6176517293721499259.jpg" width="636" height="382">

    <img src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/6176517293721499259/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_6176517293721499259.jpg" width="636" height=382 />
</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
     <p>
       
       Natasha Magnan, who runs the&nbsp;White Swan Inn in Dunstable, Bedfordshire, shared the pub's CCTV footage, which showed the pint fall off a table on Sunday night at around 7.30pm. Ms Magnan has worked at the pub for the last 20 years and said there have been several 'unusual sightings of ghosts' by staff and customers. The 37-year-old said she felt like someone was 'watching' her when she went down to the cellar last week and other staff had reported seeing strange figures in the building. The CCTV footage shows the glass standing on a table as customers sit chatting nearby before it suddenly topples over, despite none of the drinkers touching it.
     </p>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="131"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/femail/article-10511243/Cat-left-NO-EYES-string-neglect-TikTok-star-millions-fans.html">Feline her way around! Persian cat who was left with NO EYES after being neglected becomes a TikTok star with videos that show her navigating life</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/femail/article-10511243/Cat-left-NO-EYES-string-neglect-TikTok-star-millions-fans.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/14/54179951-0-image-a-5_1644848306651.jpg" alt="Cat left with NO EYES after a string of neglect becomes TikTok star with millions of fans" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/14/54179951-0-image-a-5_1644848306651.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Cat left with NO EYES after a string of neglect becomes TikTok star with millions of fans" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Eight-year-old Persian cat Moet, (pictured) who lives in Nottingham with owner Emily Shotter, 51, lost her eyes after living on the streets of Oman has found worldwide TikTok fame. She had her eyeballs removed as a kitten after living on the streets without food, water and a safe place to sleep, which led to the deterioration of her vision. She was found in a dirty cage and just a litter box to lie on. She was rescued by a local charity before being adopted just weeks after, by Emily Shotter, 51, from Nottingham, in 2015, who had only popped in to get food supplies for her other cat.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

  </h2>

     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/2753437016048316850/636x382_MP4_2753437016048316850.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/2753437016048316850/308x174_JPG_2753437016048316850.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="70" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/2753437016048316850/636x382_JPG-HD_2753437016048316850.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/2753437016048316850/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_2753437016048316850.jpg" width="636" height="382">

                <div class="article article-tri-headline">
  <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
    <a href="/news/article-10510163/Hundreds-birds-suddenly-drop-sky-Mexico-leaving-dead-bodies-sidewalk-Video.html">Bizarre moment hundreds of birds suddenly drop from the sky in Mexico leaving dead bodies strewn across the sidewalk&nbsp;</a>
  </h2>
  <a href="/news/article-10510163/Hundreds-birds-suddenly-drop-sky-Mexico-leaving-dead-bodies-sidewalk-Video.html">
    
     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/584555944666614312/636x382_MP4_584555944666614312.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/584555944666614312/308x174_JPG_584555944666614312.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="49" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/584555944666614312/636x382_JPG-HD_584555944666614312.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="49" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/584555944666614312/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_584555944666614312.jpg" width="636" height="382">
   
<noscript>
    <img src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/584555944666614312/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_584555944666614312.jpg" width="636" height=382 />
</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
     <p>
       
       Police were called to the scene&nbsp;at around 8.30am on February 7 after local residents reported hundreds of dead birds&nbsp;strewn across the sidewalk&nbsp;in the Alvaro Obregon area of Cuauhtemoc, a city in the Mexican state of Chihuahua. Shocking footage, which has gone viral on social media, shows the flock suddenly drop to the ground. Some of the birds recovered and were seen flying away but dozens remained dead on the street. Separate footage shows the yellow-headed blackbirds being swept into piles. A veterinarian who examined the dead birds suggested they could have died as a result of inhaling toxic fumes, perhaps from a heater, or electrocution after perching on power lines.
     </p>
    </div>

  </h2>

     <img data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/216361379358686902/636x382_MP4_216361379358686902.mp4" data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/216361379358686902/308x174_JPG_216361379358686902.jpg" data-frame-width="308" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-count="42" data-fps="7" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/216361379358686902/636x382_JPG-HD_216361379358686902.jpg" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-count="42" data-hd-fps="7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/216361379358686902/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_216361379358686902.jpg" width="636" height="382">
   
<noscript>
    <img src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2022/02/14/216361379358686902/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_216361379358686902.jpg" width="636" height=382 />
</noscript>

  </a>
  <div class="articletext">
    <div>
     <p>
       
       Seven-month-old Otto was being filmed by his father Ben Millner as he looked out of a large window at the&nbsp;£490-a-night Cheetah Safari Lodge at West Midlands Safari Park in Bewdley,&nbsp;Worcestershire. The baby appeared to spot something in the pitch blackness outside moments before the cheetah suddenly pounced, hitting the reinforced glass with a thud. Otto appeared unfazed and fearlessly continued watching the big cat as it turned round to face him in the footage, filmed on January 29.
     </p>
    </div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="158"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10509411/Fire-crews-race-save-woman-gets-stuck-tree-trying-rescue-PARROT.html">Fire service are called out to rescue woman stuck in a tree after climbing up to rescue pet PARROT</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10509411/Fire-crews-race-save-woman-gets-stuck-tree-trying-rescue-PARROT.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/10/54170101-0-image-a-31_1644832813298.jpg" alt="Fire crews race to save woman after she gets stuck in a tree trying to rescue her PARROT&nbsp;" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/10/54170101-0-image-a-31_1644832813298.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Fire crews race to save woman after she gets stuck in a tree trying to rescue her PARROT " />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Firefighters used a ladder to bring the woman down to ground level in Woodlands Edge, Trowbridge, on Saturday morning. Leanne Jones, 32, was eating her lunch with her baby macaw Missy on Friday afternoon when she flew away into a tree. She stayed outside with her all night waiting for her to come down by herself, but the next morning the branch snapped and Missy flapped towards another tree. Leanne's sister Toni-Anne, 33, tried to scale the tree in Woodlands Edge, Trowbridge herself to reach the bird, but got stuck.
        </p>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="159"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/travel/travel_news/article-10498685/Studio-Ghibli-theme-park-November-opening-attraction-based-anime-Japans-Walt-Disney.html">Revealed: The £218million theme park based on anime films by Japan's answer to Walt Disney is set to open this November</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/travel/travel_news/article-10498685/Studio-Ghibli-theme-park-November-opening-attraction-based-anime-Japans-Walt-Disney.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/54182963-0-image-a-2_1644852643993.jpg" alt="Studio Ghibli theme park: November opening for attraction based on anime by Japan's Walt" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/15/54182963-0-image-a-2_1644852643993.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Studio Ghibli theme park: November opening for attraction based on anime by Japan's Walt" />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            A theme park based on the anime films of Studio Ghibli, renowned for titles including the Oscar-winning Spirited Away, will open in Japan's central Aichi region on November 1. The studio has also unveiled a series of renderings that offer a glimpse at what the park will look like. 'Ghibli Park' will be divided up into five areas - three of which will open in November. In the main image, a rendering shows the 'Hill of Youth' section, where visitors will find the 'World Emporium' - the antique shop that features in the 1995 film Whisper of the Heart. The inset picture shows Studio Ghibli co-founder Hayao Miyazaki. Pictured top left is the park's life-size model of the house where the main characters of the 1988 classic My Neighbor Totoro lived, and bottom left is a rendering of The Valley of Witches area in the park, which will be inspired by the films Kiki's Delivery Service and Howl's Moving Castle.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

                <div itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem" itemprop="itemListElement" class="article article-tri-headline">
     <meta itemprop="position" content="162"> 
    <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
        <a itemprop="url" href="/news/article-10510319/Homeless-cat-alarming-likeness-LENIN-looking-private-ownership.html">Struggle of the purr-letariat! Homeless cat has alarming likeness to LENIN</a>
    </h2>
    <div class="articletext">
        <a href="/news/article-10510319/Homeless-cat-alarming-likeness-LENIN-looking-private-ownership.html">
                 <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/09/54169521-0-image-a-24_1644832175209.jpg" alt="Homeless cat with alarming likeness to LENIN is looking for private ownership&nbsp;" style="max-width:100%" width="636" height="382">
            
            
            
            
              <noscript>
            
                <img  src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/14/09/54169521-0-image-a-24_1644832175209.jpg" height="382" width="636" alt="Homeless cat with alarming likeness to LENIN is looking for private ownership " />
            
              </noscript>
            
        </a>
        <div>
        <p>
            
            Three-year-old Pavlova, a former stray, was taken in by the RSPCA's Middlesex North West and South Hertfordshire branch in January. A family had been feeding her and had even made her a wooden box shelter to sleep in over Christmas - but handed her in when they became concerned for her welfare at the end of last month. Charity workers now say the mustachioed moggy would be best suited to a 'quiet,&nbsp;adult-only home without other pets', ideally with some outside space for her to explore. They are hoping Pavlova's striking 'moustache' - which appears similar in style to the goatee sported by Bolshevik politician&nbsp;Vladimir Ilyich Ulyanov, better known as 'Lenin' -&nbsp;will help give her an edge in landing a forever home. The resemblance to the former Soviet leader is not simply one of appearance either, as she is known to be quite 'nervous' and will 'hiss' at charity workers - perhaps comparable to Lenin, who was known for his fiery temper and who suffered a number of strokes, possibly due to the pressure of reforming Tsarist Russia into a socialist paradise.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

    <span class="linktext">
        <span class="readerCommentNo bold" rel="10510319">58</span> comments
    </span>

property\n* Measure whether an ad is serving in a suitable editorial environment (brand-safe) context\n* Determine the percentage of the ad that had the opportunity to be seen and the duration of that native ads) were delivered to and interacted with by a user.\n* Apply panel- or similarly derived audience insights data to ad measurement data without a Legal Basis to apply market research to can:\n* Provide aggregate reporting to advertisers or their representatives about the audiences reached by their ads, through panel-based and similarly derived insights.\n* Provide aggregate reporting to publishers about the audiences that were served or interacted with content and/or ads on their property by applying panel-based and similarly derived insights.\n* Associate offline data with an online user for the purposes of market research to generate audience insights if vendors have declared to match and combine offline data sources (Feature 1)\n* Combine this information with other information previously collected including from across websites and apps. \nVendors cannot:\n* Measure the performance and effectiveness of ads that a specific user was served or interacted with, without a Legal Basis to measure ad performance.\n* Measure which content a specific user was served and how they interacted with it, without a Legal Basis to measure content
